{% call components.section("Usage") -%}

  <h3>Layout</h3>
  <p>A footer group is the lowest in hierarchy and should be used at the very bottom of every page.</p>

  <h3>Modular footer</h3>
  <p>Global footer content is boilerplate and relates to Red Hat as an organization. It should be used on every website, even without a modular footer. Content that is unique and has the potential to change should not appear in the global footer.</p>

  <h3>Global footer</h3>
  <p>Modular footer content is customizable and should relate closely to the specific website that it’s used on.</p>

  <h3>Vertical height</h3>
  <p>Including too much content in either layout will increase the vertical height of the footer group, especially on small screens.</p>

{%- endcall %}

<hr class="margin-top--2 margin-bottom--10">

{% call components.section("Best practices") -%}

  <p>Don’t put any unique content in the global footer that can’t be used on every website.</p>

  {% call components.example(palette='wrong') %}
  <div class="inline-flex centered margin-top--1 margin-bottom--1">
    <img src="{{ '/assets/avatar/avatar-wrong-without-text.png' | url }}">
  </div>
  {%- endcall %}

    <p>Don’t change the stacking order of layouts in the footer group.</p>

  {% call components.example(palette='wrong') %}
  <div class="inline-flex centered margin-top--1 margin-bottom--1">
    <img src="{{ '/assets/avatar/avatar-wrong-without-text.png' | url }}">
  </div>
  {%- endcall %}

  <p>A modular footer can’t live on its own, but the global footer can. Don’t omit the global footer from the footer group.</p>

  {% call components.example(palette='wrong') %}
  <div class="inline-flex centered margin-top--1 margin-bottom--1">
    <img src="{{ '/assets/avatar/avatar-wrong-without-text.png' | url }}">
