{% call components.section("Behavior") -%}

  <h3>States</h3>
  <p>When a modular footer displays accordions on small screens, they have collapsed and expanded states that hide or reveal content when toggled. By default, they load with all panels collapsed, enabling users to get a high-level overview of the content.</p>

  <h3>Multiple panels</h3>
  <p>When a modular footer contains multiple accordion panels, they can be expanded simultaneously or they can stack. Expanding one panel doesn’t collapse another which makes it easy for users to see content in the same view.</p>

  {% call components.example(palette='light') %}
  <div class="multi-column--min-200-wide margin-top--1 margin-bottom--1">
    <img src="{{ '/assets/avatar/avatar-responsive-2.png' | url }}">
  </div>
  {%- endcall %}

  <h3>Responsive design</h3>
  <p>Content in a modular footer will move into an accordion on smaller screens whereas content in the global footer will stack.</p>

{%- endcall %}

